.TH "bee-install" "1" "2012-08-31" "bee @BEE_VERSION@" "bee - bau et einfach"

.SH "NAME"
bee\-install \- Install a bee package

.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.SY "bee install"
.OP options
.I <bee-package>
.YS

.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.P
.B bee-install
is used to install a bee package.
.P
Normally
.B bee-install
searches
.B BEE_PKGDIR
for
.I <bee-package>
but you can use
.BI /path/to/ <bee-package> .bee.tar.bz2
too.

.SH "OPTIONS"
.TP
.B \-f, \-\-force
Prevent
.B bee-install
from checking whether
.I <bee-package>
is already installed.
.TP
.B \-u, \-\-update, \-\-upgrade
Update an installed
.IR <bee-package> .
.TP
.B \-n, \-\-noop
Do not install. Just print which files would be installed.
.TP
.B \-r, \-\-remove-all
When updating: Remove all older versions of the package.
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print a little help screen.

.SH "ENVIRONMENT"
.TP
.B BEE_PKGDIR
.RS
Directory searched for available bee packages

